Canal Cove Villas is a luxury project developed by Nakheel Properties, located on the renowned Palm Jumeirah in Dubai. Completed in 2007, this complex comprises a mix of villas and townhouses, boasting a Mediterranean-inspired architectural style.
Property Details
In total, there are 118 buildings within Canal Cove Villas, divided into six zones, each containing 6 to 12 buildings. Each zone features its own courtyard with a swimming pool, providing residents with exclusive leisure facilities. The properties within Canal Cove Villas offer a choice of 3 and 4-bedroom homes, starting from 3,800 sq ft in size. The starting price for these properties begins at AED 8,000,000 (USD 2,178,000) as of 2020.
Location and Accessibility
Canal Cove Villas offer a private oceanfront location on Palm Jumeirah, providing residents with a serene environment away from the bustling city. However, it remains conveniently close to the main infrastructure of Dubai. The development is easily accessible, with Dubai International Airport reachable within 30 minutes by car. The Business Bay business district and the iconic Burj Khalifa skyscraper in the Downtown area are both approximately a 20-minute drive away.
The Palm Jumeirah island itself offers a plethora of attractions and facilities for residents. Nearby attractions include the Aquaventure Waterpark, The Pointe, and Nakheel Mall, providing entertainment, dining, and shopping options. Additionally, the area is home to several nurseries, clinics, and schools, ensuring convenience for families residing in Canal Cove Villas.
Canal Cove Villas on Palm Jumeirah offer luxury waterfront living with Mediterranean charm. With its exclusive amenities, convenient location, and proximity to key attractions and facilities, it presents an ideal residential option for discerning individuals and families seeking upscale living in Dubai.

Architectural Design
Nad Al Sheba Gardens boasts a contemporary architectural design with several distinctive features:


Abundant Natural Light: The design maximizes natural daylight, with large windows and high ceilings that allow light to flow freely throughout the properties.


Modern Living Spaces: The layout and design of the properties are tailored to cater to the needs of a modern lifestyle, emphasizing comfort and functionality.


Community Features
This gated community is designed to offer residents an exclusive and tranquil environment:

Investment Potential

High ROI: The return on investment for properties in this community is appealing, with four-bedroom villas, in particular, showing a noteworthy return on investment of 5.6%.


Diverse Property Options: Whether you're considering a one-bedroom apartment or a five-bedroom villa, there are various property types to choose from, each with its own investment potential.

After 15 years of lying inactive, the Palm Jebel Ali project has been restarted, and many of us are interested to see how the new palm will turn out.
Dredging for the Palm Jebel Ali began in 2002, and work on it ended in 2008. The island, which is twice the size of Palm Jumeirah, has lain inactive ever since, despite rumors last year that Nakheel will be restarting the project and altering its name.
Facts:

There will be a total of seven interconnected islands.
The artificial island will be 13.4 sq km in size, double that of Palm Jumeirah.
It will extend Dubai's shoreline by 110 kilometres.
On the island, 80 hotels and resorts will be built.
There will be about 35,000 families living there.
All public buildings will use renewable energy to power 30% of them.

With 110km of coastline, twice the size of the Palm Jumeirah, the beaches and greenery will provide a high standard of living for its citizens, while more than 80 hotels, malls, and attractions will be available to tourists and visitors.
